Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:30 p.m. close.  The Taiex Index fell 27.07, or 0.3 percent, to 9,006.61.
The stock advanced 0.3 percent this week.  Formosa Plastics Group companies:  Formosa Chemicals & Fibre
Corp. (1326)  (1326 TT) lost 1.4 percent to NT$108.  Nan Ya Plastics
Corp. (1303)  (1303 TT) retreated 1.2 percent to NT$83.  Formosa Plastics Group put out a fire at its oil and
petrochemicals complex in the Mailiao township this morning,
Frank Fu, a Taipei-based company spokesman, said by phone today.  Formosa Chemicals halted its No. 1 aromatics plant, the
company said in a statement. Nan Ya Plastics said in its own
statement that losses from the fire will be limited as the
company draws on its inventories.  Sonix Technology Co. (5471 TT) climbed 2 percent to
NT$65.70, the highest level since Jan. 28. The company forecast
second-quarter revenue to jump 50 percent from current quarter,
Digitimes reported. Pan Ming Huang, a spokesman for Sonix,
didnâ€™t return a phone call seeking comment.  Richtek Technology Corp. (6286)  (6286 TT), a Sonix rival, surged
6.9 percent to NT$210, the most since Sept. 21. The Digitimes
report drove speculation the integrated circuit industry will
perform better than expected, said Jack Hung, an analyst at Mega
